          "body": "Verses 23-25 transition from the LORD's victory to Israel's mop-up. The tribes who were dismissed (Naphtali, Asher, Manasseh) are recalled; Ephraim seizes the Jordan fords; the Midianite princes Oreb and Zeeb are captured and executed. The named landmarks — *Rock of the Raven*, *Winepress of the Wolf* — become memorials cited centuries later (Psalm 83:11; Isaiah 9:4; 10:26) as Israel's archetypal night of deliverance. But the chapter ends with a foreshadow: Gideon will *send* (*shalach*, v.24) the messengers, just as he will *send* the call that gathers his own following. The man who refused credit in chapter 7 will demand it in chapter 8. The chapter's spiritual high point makes the coming fall the more tragic."
